Class PcBuildController

java.lang.Object
be.thomasmore.pcbuilder.controllers.user.PcBuildController
@Controller @RequestMapping("/user") public class PcBuildController extends Object
Controller for handling PC build operations including creating, editing, viewing, deleting, and listing PC builds.

  • Method Details

    • createPcBuild

      @ModelAttribute("pcBuild") public PcBuild createPcBuild(@PathVariable(required=false) Integer id)
      Creates or retrieves a PC build based on the provided ID. If the ID is null, a new PC build is created.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the PC build to retrieve, can be null for a new build.
      Returns:
      the PcBuild object to be used in the view.

    • addOrEditPcBuild

      @GetMapping({"/addbuild","/editbuild/{id}"}) public String addOrEditPcBuild(@PathVariable(required=false) Integer id, org.springframework.ui.Model model)
      Adds or edits a PC build depending on whether an ID is provided. This method retrieves the relevant components from repositories and prepares them for use in the view.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the PC build to edit, can be null for adding a new build.
      model - the model object to store attributes for the view.
      Returns:
      the name of the template to render.

    • addOrEditPcBuildPost

      @PostMapping({"/addbuild","/editbuild/{id}"}) public String addOrEditPcBuildPost(@ModelAttribute PcBuild pcBuild, org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.support.RedirectAttributes redirectAttributes, Principal principal)
      Handles the POST request to either add a new PC build or edit an existing one. This method also validates the compatibility of selected components.
      Parameters:
      pcBuild - the PC build object containing selected components.
      redirectAttributes - the redirect attributes to pass flash messages.
      Returns:
      a redirect URL based on the success or failure of the operation.

    • viewPcBuild

      @GetMapping("/viewbuild/{id}") public String viewPcBuild(@PathVariable Integer id, org.springframework.ui.Model model, Principal principal)
      Views the details of a specific PC build.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the PC build to view.
      model - the model object to store attributes for the view.
      Returns:
      the name of the template to render.

    • viewPcBuilds

      @GetMapping("/pcbuilds") public String viewPcBuilds(org.springframework.ui.Model model, Principal principal)
      Lists all PC builds.
      Parameters:
      model - the model object to store attributes for the view.
      Returns:
      the name of the template to render.

    • deletePcBuild

      @GetMapping("/deletebuild/{id}") public String deletePcBuild(@PathVariable Integer id)
      Handles the request to delete a PC build.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the PC build to delete.
      Returns:
      a redirect URL to the list of PC builds.
